The planned analytic sample size is 144. After achieving that
sample, planned analyses will be run. If a significant effect is found,
sampling stops. If a significant effect in the prediction direction is
not found, a second round of data collection will collect data from
128 additional observations, for a pooled analytic sample of 272.
Sampling will stop after the second round of data collection
regardless of a significant effect.
This stopping rule is required for the testing of H* in all SCORE
projects.
In order to achieve the necessary sample size, we will recruit 160
participants (this is to account for any data losses and incomplete
data in the lab). If a significant effect in the prediction direction is
not found, the second round of data collection will collect data from
140 additional observations, for a pooled analytic sample of 300.
Sampling will stop after the second round of data collection
regardless of a significant effect.
