We plan to manipulate social observation between subjects, using
social observation paradigm. There will be two groups: observed
and unobserved (control). Participants in the observed group will
be told that their performances will be monitored and manually
recorded by two experimenters due to some technical glitch that
may cause data loss (Izuma et al., 2010). To increase credibility of
the manipulation, participants will be introduced to an ostensibly-
real experimental setup for social observation: they will be brought
to a separate cubicle wherein two
experimenters (one male and one female observer) will be sitting
with a monitoring device connected to the participants’ own screen.
Participants in the control group will be told that their responses
will be spontaneously encrypted and will remain anonymous after
the experiment. Detailed description of the manipulation can be
found in the Study Protocol, https://osf.io/vscu8/?
view_only=ca6e17c6f1844a4aab51ca749185308e).
Additionally, we will manipulate the dilemma type within
participants. There will be 3 types of dilemmas: personal-moral
dilemmas, impersonal-moral dilemmas and nonmoral control
dilemmas (all presented in Study Materials).
In experimental manipulations, we will directly follow the
procedures of the original study.
